wikipedia_page.main: Alan Street (born 17 April 1982) is a British former competitive figure skater. He is the 2001 British national champion in men's singles. He competed at four World Junior Championships, achieving his best result, sixth, in 2001 (Sofia, Bulgaria). He also appeared at one senior international, the 2001 European Championships, where he placed 28th. He trained in Blackburn and Ayr.
